INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '9c32a607-2fdc-4ffe-b71c-4808bb156cd8',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$LlamaIndex — VectorStoreIndex vs SummaryIndex: Picking the Right Retrieval Strategy$escape$,
  $escape$LlamaIndex exposes multiple index types that trade off differently depending on your retrieval pattern. `VectorStoreIndex` chunks documents into `Node` objects, embeds them, and retrieves by semantic similarity — ideal for large corpora where you need top-k relevant passages. `SummaryIndex` (formerly `ListIndex`) iterates over all nodes sequentially, making it better for summarization tasks over small, bounded document sets.

When loading, `SimpleDirectoryReader` handles PDFs, Markdown, and DOCX automatically. For fine-grained control, set `chunk_size` and `chunk_overlap` on `SentenceSplitter` before indexing — defaults (1024/20) are often too coarse for dense technical docs.

Query engines sit on top of indexes. `as_query_engine()` returns a `RetrieverQueryEngine` with a built-in synthesizer. Swap the retriever via `index.as_retriever(similarity_top_k=8)` and plug it into a `RouterQueryEngine` to fan queries across multiple indexes — useful when documents live in different domains. For hybrid retrieval, combine `BM25Retriever` with a vector retriever using `QueryFusionRetriever` with `mode=QueryFusionMode.RECIPROCAL_RANK`.$escape$,
  $escape$from llama_index.core import VectorStoreIndex, SimpleDirectoryReader
from llama_index.core.node_parser import SentenceSplitter
from llama_index.retrievers.bm25 import BM25Retriever
from llama_index.core.retrievers import QueryFusionRetriever, QueryFusionMode

docs = SimpleDirectoryReader("./docs").load_data()
splitter = SentenceSplitter(chunk_size=512, chunk_overlap=64)
nodes = splitter.get_nodes_from_documents(docs)

index = VectorStoreIndex(nodes)
vector_retriever = index.as_retriever(similarity_top_k=6)
bm25_retriever = BM25Retriever.from_defaults(nodes=nodes, similarity_top_k=6)

hybrid_retriever = QueryFusionRetriever(
    [vector_retriever, bm25_retriever],
    mode=QueryFusionMode.RECIPROCAL_RANK,
    num_queries=1,
)
query_engine = index.as_query_engine(retriever=hybrid_retriever)
response = query_engine.query("How does attention masking work in transformers?")
print(response)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
